'''Androbulus''' was a sculptor in [[classical antiquity]]. He was mentioned by [[Pliny the Elder]] as having been celebrated as a maker of statues of philosophers.<ref>[[Pliny the Elder]], ''[[Natural History (Pliny)|Natural History]]'' xxxiv. 19. § 26</ref>

