'''L'Institut de recherche d'Hydro-Québec''' ''(Hydro-Québec Research Institute)'', known by its acronym '''IREQ''' ("Institut de recherche en électricité du Québec", ''Quebec Electricity Research Institute'') is a [[research institute]] established in 1967 by [[Government-owned corporation|government-owned]] [[public utility|utility]] [[Hydro-Québec]]. IREQ operates from [[Varennes, Quebec|Varennes]], a town on the south shore of [[Montreal]], [[Quebec]], Canada.<ref name="IREQ">{{cite news |first=Johanne |last=Gauthier |title=L’IREQ : leader de l’innovation technologique à Hydro-Québec |work=Choc |date=October 2007 |volume=25 |issue=2 |pages=26–29 |url=http://www.aieq.net/_site/documents/applications/pdf/ChocOct07-IREQ.pdf |language=French |format=PDF |accessdate=2009-03-20 }}{{dead link|date=November 2017 |bot=InternetArchiveBot |fix-attempted=yes }}</ref> IREQ operates on an annual research budget of approximately $100 million<ref>{{cite book |title=Shaping The Future : Annual Report 2009 |author=Hydro-Québec |location=Montreal |year=2010 |isbn=978-2-550-58101-7 |url=http://www.hydroquebec.com/publications/en/annual_report/pdf/annual-report-2009.pdf |page=32 |issn=0702-6706 |accessdate=2010-10-09|ref=harv}}</ref> and specializes in the areas of high voltage, [[mechanics]] and thermomechanics, network simulations and calibration.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.hydroquebec.com/technologie/index.html |title=Hydro-Québec Research Institute |author=Hydro-Québec Technologie|accessdate=2010-10-09}}</ref>
In the last 20 years, the institute has also conducted [[research and development]] work towards the [[electric vehicle|electrification of ground transportation]]. Current projects include [[battery (electricity)|battery]] advanced materials, including work on [[Molten salt battery|molten salts]], [[lithium iron phosphate]] and [[titanate|nanotitanate]],<ref>{{harvnb|Hydro-Québec|2010|p=34}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|title=Moteur électrique: percée majeure chez Hydro-Québec|first=Sébastien|last=Templier|work=[[La Presse (Canadian newspaper)|La Presse]]|location=Montreal|date=16 October 2009|url=http://lapresseaffaires.cyberpresse.ca/economie/automobile/200910/16/01-911848-moteur-electrique-percee-majeure-chez-hydro-quebec.php|language=French|accessdate=2009-11-18|deadurl=yes|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20091203074451/http://lapresseaffaires.cyberpresse.ca/economie/automobile/200910/16/01-911848-moteur-electrique-percee-majeure-chez-hydro-quebec.php|archivedate=3 December 2009|df=}}</ref> improved electric [[powertrain|drive train]]s and the impacts of the large scale deployment of electric vehicles on the [[electrical grid|power grid]].<ref>{{cite web|author=Hydro-Québec |url=http://www.hydroquebec.com/transportation-electrification/action-plan.html |year=2010 |title=Transportation Electricification: Action Plan |accessdate=2010-10-09 }}</ref> Projects focus on technologies to increase [[range (vehicle)|range]], improve performance in [[cold weather]] and reduce [[rechargeable battery|charging time]].<ref>{{cite news |first=François |last=Cardinal |title=Une batterie dans les cartons d'Hydro-Québec |work=[[La Presse (Canadian newspaper)|La Presse]] |location=Montreal |language=French |date=19 November 2008 |url=http://monvolant.cyberpresse.ca/dossiers/la-folie-de-lhybride/200811/19/01-802158-une-batterie-dans-les-cartons-dhydro-quebec.php |accessdate=2009-03-28 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20110706175219/http://monvolant.cyberpresse.ca/dossiers/la-folie-de-lhybride/200811/19/01-802158-une-batterie-dans-les-cartons-dhydro-quebec.php |archivedate=6 July 2011 |df= }}</ref>
